    "body": "Similar to `request_class`, `response_class` and `app_ctx_globals_class`, the `config_class` attribute of `Flask` allows to specify custom class that stores the configuration for the app:\n\n``` python\nimport flask\n\nclass Config(flask.Config):\n    def __getitem__(self, key):\n        try:\n            return super(Config, self).__getitem__(key)\n        except KeyError:\n            return None\n\nclass Flask(flask.Flask):\n    config_class = Config\n```\n\nThe current alternative is to override `make_config` and repeat its logic (such as handling of `instance_relative` argument). This should be more convenient and robust.\n",
